**MRO & MAINTENANCE SHOP PARTNERSHIP PROGRAM**

Add Value to Annual Inspections While Generating Incremental Revenue

Program Overview

Provenarc Aero Solutions partners with aircraft maintenance facilities to integrate
professional records digitization services into the annual inspection
and routine maintenance workflow. Our program transforms logbook access
from a friction point into a value-added service that differentiates
your shop, increases customer satisfaction, and generates incremental
revenue without adding labor or equipment costs.

The Business Case for Maintenance Shops

Reduce Your AD Research Time

Airworthiness Directive compliance verification is one of the most
time-consuming elements of annual inspections. IAs currently spend
4--15+ hours per annual manually cross-referencing logbook entries
against AD databases. With digitized, searchable records, your mechanics
can type an AD number and instantly retrieve all compliance entries
across decades of logbook history. For a shop performing 50--100+
annuals per year, the labor savings compound significantly.

Enhance Customer Retention

Aircraft owners increasingly expect modern, digital services. Offering
professional records digitization as part of the annual inspection
positions your shop as a forward-thinking partner rather than a
commodity service provider. Customers who receive digitized records
during their annual are more likely to return year after year because
you have demonstrated investment in their aircraft\'s long-term value
preservation.

Generate Incremental Revenue from Existing Traffic

Every aircraft entering your shop for an annual inspection or 100-hour
inspection represents an existing customer relationship and logbook
access. Adding a \$350--\$500 digitization service to your annual
invoice creates a 10--20% upsell opportunity with minimal sales effort.
For a shop performing 50 annuals per year at 30% adoption, the
incremental revenue ranges from \$5,250 to \$7,500 annually. For a shop
performing 100+ annuals, the opportunity scales to \$10,500--\$15,000+
annually.

Zero Capital Investment Required

You do not need to purchase scanning equipment, hire additional staff,
or develop expertise in document archiving. Provenarc Aero Solutions provides all
hardware, software, logistics, quality control, and customer support.
Your shop simply offers the service, collects payment as a line item on
the invoice, and coordinates logbook pickup with Provenarc Aero Solutions. We handle
the rest.

How the Program Works: Step-by-Step

1.  **Customer Brings Aircraft for Annual Inspection**

When a customer schedules an annual inspection or 100-hour inspection,
your front desk or service writer presents the digitization option. This
can be done verbally during check-in or included as a pre-printed line
item on your work order form. Example language: \"Add professional
logbook digitization by Provenarc Aero Solutions --- \$500.\" The decision is
binary: the customer either adds it to the service package or declines.

2.  **Provenarc Aero Solutions Picks Up Logbooks on Day 1**

If the customer opts in, your shop notifies Provenarc Aero Solutions via phone,
email, or text message. Provenarc Aero Solutions schedules pickup for Day 1 of the
annual inspection (the same day the aircraft enters your shop). We
arrive on-site, collect the logbooks, provide a signed receipt, and
transport the documents to our secure scanning facility. No logbooks are
ever shipped via FedEx, UPS, or USPS. All transport is by personal
vehicle or aircraft.

3.  **Scanning and Digitization (1--3 Business Days)**

Provenarc Aero Solutions performs complete digitization including high-resolution
scanning (300 DPI minimum), optical character recognition for text
searchability, organized folder structure by log type, and quality
control review of every page. Turnaround time is 1--3 business days for
typical single-engine piston aircraft, which aligns perfectly with the
1--3 week duration of most annual inspections. The logbooks are returned
to your shop well before the annual is completed.

4.  **Logbooks Returned to Your Shop**

Provenarc Aero Solutions returns the physical logbooks to your shop along with the
customer\'s encrypted USB drive and secure cloud download link. Your
shop receives a complimentary digital copy of the scanned records at no
charge, which your mechanics can reference during future inspections.
This reduces your AD research time on the next annual for this aircraft.
The customer receives their logbooks back in archival-quality storage
boxes when they pick up their aircraft.

5.  **Customer Picks Up Aircraft with Digital Records**

When the annual inspection is complete and the customer picks up their
aircraft, they also receive their digitized records. This creates a
high-touch customer experience where the annual inspection becomes more
than routine maintenance---it becomes a comprehensive aircraft care
package that includes both airworthiness compliance and asset value
preservation.

Pricing Structure and Revenue Sharing

Option 1: Wholesale Pricing (Shop Retains Full Margin)

Your shop charges the customer the full retail price and pays Aero
Records a wholesale rate. You retain the margin as additional profit on
the annual inspection.

**Wholesale pricing to your shop:**

-   Single-engine piston (existing digital file update): \$280 wholesale

-   Single-engine piston (first-time full digitization): \$550 wholesale

-   Twin-engine piston or complex single: \$700 wholesale

**Suggested retail pricing to customer:**

-   Existing digital file update: \$350--\$400 retail

-   First-time full digitization: \$750--\$850 retail

-   Twin/complex: \$900--\$1,000 retail

**Your margin:** \$70--\$300 per job depending on aircraft type and
whether it is a first-time digitization or an annual update.

**Example economics (50 annuals per year, 30% adoption):** 15 jobs
annually. Average margin: \$100 per job. Annual incremental profit:
\$1,500. For shops performing 100+ annuals: \$3,000+ annual incremental
profit.

Option 2: Referral Commission (Provenarc Aero Solutions Invoices Customer)

Your shop refers the customer to Provenarc Aero Solutions. We invoice the customer
directly under our brand. You receive a commission for every completed
referral.

**Commission structure:**

-   \$50 per completed job (any aircraft type)

-   Paid within 30 days of service completion

-   No minimum volume required

**Example economics (50 annuals per year, 30% adoption):** 15 referrals
annually. Commission: \$50 per referral. Annual passive income: \$750.
For shops performing 100+ annuals: \$1,500 annual passive income.

**Best for:** Shops that prefer simplicity and minimal administrative
overhead. Provenarc Aero Solutions handles all customer communication, invoicing,
and payment collection. Your shop simply makes the introduction.

Option 3: Hourly Shop Rate

For shops that prefer to invoice by the hour rather than as a flat-rate
add-on, Provenarc Aero Solutions provides digitization services at a wholesale
hourly rate that you can mark up to your standard shop labor rate.

**Wholesale hourly rate:** \$75 per hour

**Typical time required:** 4--6 hours for single-engine piston, 8--12
hours for twin/complex

**Your shop charges customer:** \$85--\$125 per hour (your standard shop
labor rate)

**Your margin:** \$10--\$50 per hour depending on your markup, totaling
\$40--\$300 per job.

