Sample Front Desk Script

\"While your aircraft is here for the annual inspection, we now offer
professional logbook digitization by Provenarc Aero Solutions. They pick up your
logbooks on Day 1, scan everything to create a searchable digital
archive, and return the books before your annual is complete. You get an
encrypted USB drive and cloud access. The cost is \$500, which we add to
your invoice. It is optional, but many of our customers find it valuable
for protecting their records and making them easier to search. Would you
like to add that to your annual?\"

This script is concise, explains the value clearly, provides transparent
pricing, and gives the customer a binary yes/no decision without
high-pressure sales tactics.

Handling Common Customer Objections

**Objection: \"I can just scan them myself with my phone.\"**

**Response:** \"That\'s true, and many owners do start that way. The
difference is professional scanning uses high-resolution equipment with
automatic page detection, OCR for text searchability, and archival PDF/A
format that won\'t degrade over time. Phone scans often have quality
issues---shadows, glare, skipped pages---and aren\'t searchable. For a
one-time investment of \$500, you get a professional archive that holds
up in pre-buy inspections and insurance claims.\"

**Objection: \"I\'ll think about it and maybe do it next year.\"**

**Response:** \"Absolutely, it is your decision. One thing to consider:
we already have your logbooks here for the annual. If you add
digitization now, there is zero inconvenience---we pick them up while
they are already in our shop. If you wait until next year, you would
need to coordinate a separate pickup and return. Many customers find it
easier to just include it with the annual.\"

**Objection: \"My logbooks are already partially digitized.\"**

**Response:** \"Great! Provenarc Aero Solutions can update your existing digital
files with all the new entries from this annual and any other recent
maintenance. That costs less than a full digitization---typically around
\$350 instead of \$500. You keep your records current without having to
do it yourself.\"

Service Standards and Shop Benefits

Complimentary Shop Copy of All Digitized Records

Every aircraft your shop digitizes through this program results in your
shop receiving a complimentary digital copy of the scanned records at no
cost. This builds a searchable reference library of your customer
aircraft that reduces your AD research time on future annuals. Over
time, this creates a compound efficiency gain as more of your customer
base has digitized records on file.

Guaranteed Turnaround Aligned with Annual Inspection Timeline

Provenarc Aero Solutions guarantees logbook return within 3--5 business days for
single-engine piston aircraft. Since most annual inspections take 1--3
weeks, this ensures logbooks are always back in your shop before the
annual is completed. If your annual inspection timeline is accelerated
(rush jobs), Provenarc Aero Solutions can provide same-day or next-day turnaround at
no additional charge with advance notice.

No Disruption to Your Workflow

Provenarc Aero Solutions coordinates all logistics. We pick up logbooks from your
shop, transport them securely, complete all scanning and quality
control, and return them directly to your shop. Your mechanics and
service writers do not handle any part of the digitization process. The
only touchpoints for your staff are: (1) presenting the option to the
customer during check-in, and (2) handing over the logbooks to Aero
Records on Day 1 of the annual.

Professional Insurance Coverage During Transport

All logbooks transported by Provenarc Aero Solutions are covered by \$100,000
bailee\'s customer coverage during transit and while in our possession.
This protects your shop from liability in the unlikely event of loss or
damage. Your shop\'s insurance exposure does not increase by offering
this service.

Getting Started: Implementation Timeline

**Week 1: Partnership Agreement and Kickoff Meeting**

Provenarc Aero Solutions provides a standard partnership agreement covering terms,
pricing, service standards, commission payment schedules (if
applicable), and termination provisions. Agreement review and execution
typically completes within 3--5 business days. We then schedule a
60-minute on-site kickoff meeting at your shop to train your front desk
staff and service writers on how to present the service to customers.

**Week 2: Marketing Materials Deployment**

Provenarc Aero Solutions delivers all marketing materials including counter display
cards, flyers, email templates, and work order line item templates. Your
shop begins presenting the digitization option to customers scheduling
annual inspections. No minimum volume is required, so your shop can
start with one or two pilot customers to test the process before
scaling.

**Week 3--4: First Customer Jobs and Process Refinement**

As your first customers opt in, Provenarc Aero Solutions executes the workflow:
pickup on Day 1 of the annual, digitization within 1--3 business days,
and return to your shop. After the first 2--3 jobs, we schedule a brief
follow-up call to address any process questions and refine coordination
procedures. Most shops reach steady-state operations within the first
month.

Frequently Asked Questions

**What if a customer declines digitization but later changes their
mind?**

No problem. Provenarc Aero Solutions can pick up logbooks at any time, not just
during annual inspections. If a customer declines during the annual but
calls your shop six months later asking for digitization, you simply
refer them to Provenarc Aero Solutions and still earn the commission (if using the
referral model) or can invoice them directly (if using the wholesale
model). The service is not limited to annual inspection timing.

**Do we need to store any scanning equipment or software?**

No. Provenarc Aero Solutions brings all scanning equipment to our facility. Your
shop does not need to invest in any hardware, software licenses, or
storage space. The only physical items at your shop are the marketing
materials (counter display card and flyers).

**What happens if we lose a logbook or it gets damaged while in our
shop?**

Provenarc Aero Solutions assumes possession and liability for logbooks once we pick
them up from your shop. While logbooks are in your shop before we pick
them up, they remain the customer\'s responsibility and are covered by
your shop\'s normal bailee liability insurance. Once Provenarc Aero Solutions takes
possession, our \$100,000 bailee\'s coverage applies. This means your
shop\'s insurance exposure does not increase.

**Can we offer digitization to customers who are NOT getting an
annual?**

Absolutely. The annual inspection workflow is the primary use case
because you already have logbook access, but you can refer any aircraft
owner to Provenarc Aero Solutions at any time. This includes customers bringing
aircraft for oil changes, avionics upgrades, or one-time repairs. You
earn the same commission or margin regardless of what service the
aircraft is in for.

**How are commissions or wholesale payments processed?**

For the referral commission model, payments are made within 30 days of
job completion via ACH direct deposit, check, or wire transfer. Monthly
statements are provided. For the wholesale model, your shop invoices the
customer directly and pays Provenarc Aero Solutions our wholesale rate within 30
days of invoice date. Payment terms are net-30.

**Is there a minimum volume commitment?**

No. There is no minimum job volume, no exclusivity requirement, and no
upfront fees. The partnership agreement is cancellable by either party
with 30 days written notice. You offer digitization to as many or as few
customers as makes sense for your shop. If no customers opt in during a
given month, there are no penalties or obligations.

